HEADWORD: Fop
<hw>Fop</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>foppe</ets>,
<ets>fop</ets>, fool; cf. E. <ets>fob</ets> to cheat, G.
<ets>foppen</ets> to make a fool of one, jeer, D.
<ets>foppen</ets>.]</ety> <def>One whose ambition it is to gain
admiration by showy dress; a coxcomb; an inferior dandy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

